steps.description:
Once you boot up FIFA on the Wii, you will be presented with several options to pick from. If you just want to start a quick game, select “Hit the Pitch”. This will set up a quick standard game which will allow you to choose your team and your opponent. Other options include:
Intercity Cup – This allows you to pick a team and run through a tournament, earning rewards. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a2/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/a/a2/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/aid1131300-v4-728px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":267,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Hit the Streets – This starts a 5 v 5 street game. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c8/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/c/c8/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/aid1131300-v4-728px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":267,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Streets to Stadium – Allows you to create a player and follow his career, building stats. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1f/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/1/1f/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/aid1131300-v4-728px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":267,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Be a Manager – This allows you to manage a team, performing trades and training your players. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c6/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/c/c6/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet4.jpg/aid1131300-v4-728px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":267,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Tournament – Gives you a variety of tournaments to test your skills in. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e7/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/e/e7/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet5.jpg/aid1131300-v4-728px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-1Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":267,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you are using Advanced Controls, you can issue commands to your team via Quick Tactics. You can assign four different quick tactics to your controller. Use the Quick Tactics menu to choose which tactics you’d like to use. Watch the preview window to see how the tactic will generally play out on the field. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7e/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/7/7e/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/aid1131300-v4-728px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":267,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Quick tactics are not available for All-Play controls. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/91/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/91/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/aid1131300-v4-728px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":267,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Turn your player towards your intended receiver using the thumbstick and tap the A button to make a ground pass, where the ball stays low to the pitch. If you press and hold the A button, you will perform a lob pass, lifting the ball above players’ heads and travelling much farther. Holding the C button while you pass will perform a through ball, which a pass where you lead your target. This is especially useful for breakaways, as you can increase your speed and get away from opponents. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/37/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/3/37/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/aid1131300-v4-728px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":267,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

For All-Play controls, there is only one pass command (A), and the computer takes care of the rest. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/ae/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/a/ae/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/aid1131300-v4-728px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":267,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Shooting works almost exactly the same as passing. Aim your player towards the opposing goal and either tap or press the B button. This will affect the power of your shot. Hold the C button while shooting for a chip shot that you can lob over defenders’ heads. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/00/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/0/00/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/aid1131300-v4-728px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":267,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

For All-Play controls, there is only one shoot command (B), and the computer takes care of the rest. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/99/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/99/Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/aid1131300-v4-728px-Play-FIFA-on-the-Wii-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":267,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"423","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
